33static const int64_t kRetransmitWindowSizeMs = 500;
34static const size_t kMaxOverheadBytes = 500;
35
36constexpr TimeDelta kPacerQueueUpdateInterval = TimeDelta::Millis(25);
37
38TargetRateConstraints ConvertConstraints(int min_bitrate_bps,
39 int max_bitrate_bps,
40 int start_bitrate_bps,
41 Clock* clock) {
42 TargetRateConstraints msg;
43 msg.at_time = Timestamp::Millis(clock->TimeInMilliseconds());
44 msg.min_data_rate = min_bitrate_bps >= 0
45 ? DataRate::BitsPerSec(min_bitrate_bps)
46 : DataRate::Zero();
47 msg.max_data_rate = max_bitrate_bps > 0
48 ? DataRate::BitsPerSec(max_bitrate_bps)
49 : DataRate::Infinity();
50 if (start_bitrate_bps > 0)
51 msg.starting_rate = DataRate::BitsPerSec(start_bitrate_bps);
52 return msg;
53}
54
55TargetRateConstraints ConvertConstraints(const BitrateConstraints& contraints,
56 Clock* clock) {
57 return ConvertConstraints(contraints.min_bitrate_bps,
58 contraints.max_bitrate_bps,
59 contraints.start_bitrate_bps, clock);
60}
61
62bool IsEnabled(const WebRtcKeyValueConfig* trials, absl::string_view key) {
63 RTC_DCHECK(trials != nullptr);
64 return absl::StartsWith(trials->Lookup(key), "Enabled");
65}
66
67bool IsDisabled(const WebRtcKeyValueConfig* trials, absl::string_view key) {
68 RTC_DCHECK(trials != nullptr);
69 return absl::StartsWith(trials->Lookup(key), "Disabled");
70}
71
72bool IsRelayed(const rtc::NetworkRoute& route) {
73 return route.local.uses_turn() || route.remote.uses_turn();
74}

78RtpTransportControllerSend::RtpTransportControllerSend(
79 Clock* clock,
80 webrtc::RtcEventLog* event_log,
81 NetworkStatePredictorFactoryInterface* predictor_factory,
82 NetworkControllerFactoryInterface* controller_factory,
83 const BitrateConstraints& bitrate_config,
84 std::unique_ptr<ProcessThread> process_thread,
85 TaskQueueFactory* task_queue_factory,
86 const WebRtcKeyValueConfig* trials)
87 : clock_(clock),
88 event_log_(event_log),
89 bitrate_configurator_(bitrate_config),
90 pacer_started_(false),
91 process_thread_(std::move(process_thread)),
92 use_task_queue_pacer_(IsEnabled(trials, "WebRTC-TaskQueuePacer")),
93 process_thread_pacer_(use_task_queue_pacer_
94 ? nullptr
95 : new PacedSender(clock,
96 &packet_router_,
97 event_log,
98 trials,
99 process_thread_.get())),
100 task_queue_pacer_(
101 use_task_queue_pacer_
102 ? new TaskQueuePacedSender(
103 clock,
104 &packet_router_,
105 event_log,
106 trials,
107 task_queue_factory,
108 /*hold_back_window = */ PacingController::kMinSleepTime)
109 : nullptr),
110 observer_(nullptr),
111 controller_factory_override_(controller_factory),
112 controller_factory_fallback_(
113 std::make_unique<GoogCcNetworkControllerFactory>(predictor_factory)),
114 process_interval_(controller_factory_fallback_->GetProcessInterval()),
115 last_report_block_time_(Timestamp::Millis(clock_->TimeInMilliseconds())),
116 reset_feedback_on_route_change_(
117 !IsEnabled(trials, "WebRTC-Bwe-NoFeedbackReset")),
118 send_side_bwe_with_overhead_(
119 !IsDisabled(trials, "WebRTC-SendSideBwe-WithOverhead")),
120 add_pacing_to_cwin_(
121 IsEnabled(trials, "WebRTC-AddPacingToCongestionWindowPushback")),
122 relay_bandwidth_cap_("relay_cap", DataRate::PlusInfinity()),
123 transport_overhead_bytes_per_packet_(0),
124 network_available_(false),
125 retransmission_rate_limiter_(clock, kRetransmitWindowSizeMs),
126 task_queue_(task_queue_factory->CreateTaskQueue(
127 "rtp_send_controller",
128 TaskQueueFactory::Priority::NORMAL)) {
129 ParseFieldTrial({&relay_bandwidth_cap_},
130 trials->Lookup("WebRTC-Bwe-NetworkRouteConstraints"));
131 initial_config_.constraints = ConvertConstraints(bitrate_config, clock_);
132 initial_config_.event_log = event_log;
133 initial_config_.key_value_config = trials;
134 RTC_DCHECK(bitrate_config.start_bitrate_bps > 0);
135
136 pacer()->SetPacingRates(
137 DataRate::BitsPerSec(bitrate_config.start_bitrate_bps), DataRate::Zero());
138
139 if (absl::StartsWith(trials->Lookup("WebRTC-LazyPacerStart"), "Disabled")) {
140 EnsureStarted();
141 }
142}

148RtpVideoSenderInterface* RtpTransportControllerSend::CreateRtpVideoSender(
149 std::map<uint32_t, RtpState> suspended_ssrcs,
150 const std::map<uint32_t, RtpPayloadState>& states,
151 const RtpConfig& rtp_config,
152 int rtcp_report_interval_ms,
153 Transport* send_transport,
154 const RtpSenderObservers& observers,
155 RtcEventLog* event_log,
156 std::unique_ptr<FecController> fec_controller,
157 const RtpSenderFrameEncryptionConfig& frame_encryption_config,
158 rtc::scoped_refptr<FrameTransformerInterface> frame_transformer) {
159 video_rtp_senders_.push_back(std::make_unique<RtpVideoSender>(
160 clock_, suspended_ssrcs, states, rtp_config, rtcp_report_interval_ms,
161 send_transport, observers,
162 // TODO(holmer): Remove this circular dependency by injecting
163 // the parts of RtpTransportControllerSendInterface that are really used.
164 this, event_log, &retransmission_rate_limiter_, std::move(fec_controller),
165 frame_encryption_config.frame_encryptor,
166 frame_encryption_config.crypto_options, std::move(frame_transformer)));
167 return video_rtp_senders_.back().get();
168}

170void RtpTransportControllerSend::DestroyRtpVideoSender(
171 RtpVideoSenderInterface* rtp_video_sender) {
172 std::vector<std::unique_ptr<RtpVideoSenderInterface>>::iterator it =
173 video_rtp_senders_.end();
174 for (it = video_rtp_senders_.begin(); it != video_rtp_senders_.end(); ++it) {
175 if (it->get() == rtp_video_sender) {
176 break;
177 }
178 }
179 RTC_DCHECK(it != video_rtp_senders_.end());
180 video_rtp_senders_.erase(it);
181}

183void RtpTransportControllerSend::UpdateControlState() {
184 absl::optional<TargetTransferRate> update = control_handler_->GetUpdate();
185 if (!update)
186 return;
187 retransmission_rate_limiter_.SetMaxRate(update->target_rate.bps());
188 // We won't create control_handler_ until we have an observers.
189 RTC_DCHECK(observer_ != nullptr);
190 observer_->OnTargetTransferRate(*update);
191}

264bool RtpTransportControllerSend::IsRelevantRouteChange(
265 const rtc::NetworkRoute& old_route,
266 const rtc::NetworkRoute& new_route) const {
267 // TODO(bugs.webrtc.org/11438): Experiment with using more information/
268 // other conditions.
269 bool connected_changed = old_route.connected != new_route.connected;
270 bool route_ids_changed =
271 old_route.local.network_id() != new_route.local.network_id() ||
272 old_route.remote.network_id() != new_route.remote.network_id();
273 if (relay_bandwidth_cap_->IsFinite()) {
274 bool relaying_changed = IsRelayed(old_route) != IsRelayed(new_route);
275 return connected_changed || route_ids_changed || relaying_changed;
276 } else {
277 return connected_changed || route_ids_changed;
278 }
279}
280
281void RtpTransportControllerSend::OnNetworkRouteChanged(
282 const std::string& transport_name,
283 const rtc::NetworkRoute& network_route) {
284 // Check if the network route is connected.
285
286 if (!network_route.connected) {
287 // TODO(honghaiz): Perhaps handle this in SignalChannelNetworkState and
288 // consider merging these two methods.
289 return;
290 }
291
292 absl::optional<BitrateConstraints> relay_constraint_update =
293 ApplyOrLiftRelayCap(IsRelayed(network_route));
294
295 // Check whether the network route has changed on each transport.
296 auto result =
297 network_routes_.insert(std::make_pair(transport_name, network_route));
298 auto kv = result.first;
299 bool inserted = result.second;
300 if (inserted || !(kv->second == network_route)) {
301 RTC_LOG(LS_INFO) << "Network route changed on transport " << transport_name
302 << ": new_route = " << network_route.DebugString();
303 if (!inserted) {
304 RTC_LOG(LS_INFO) << "old_route = " << kv->second.DebugString();
305 }
306 }
307
308 if (inserted) {
309 if (relay_constraint_update.has_value()) {
310 UpdateBitrateConstraints(*relay_constraint_update);
311 }
312 task_queue_.PostTask([this, network_route] {
313 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(&task_queue_);
314 transport_overhead_bytes_per_packet_ = network_route.packet_overhead;
315 });
316 // No need to reset BWE if this is the first time the network connects.
317 return;
318 }
319
320 const rtc::NetworkRoute old_route = kv->second;
321 kv->second = network_route;
322
323 // Check if enough conditions of the new/old route has changed
324 // to trigger resetting of bitrates (and a probe).
325 if (IsRelevantRouteChange(old_route, network_route)) {
326 BitrateConstraints bitrate_config = bitrate_configurator_.GetConfig();
327 RTC_LOG(LS_INFO) << "Reset bitrates to min: "
328 << bitrate_config.min_bitrate_bps
329 << " bps, start: " << bitrate_config.start_bitrate_bps
330 << " bps, max: " << bitrate_config.max_bitrate_bps
331 << " bps.";
332 RTC_DCHECK_GT(bitrate_config.start_bitrate_bps, 0);
333
334 if (event_log_) {
335 event_log_->Log(std::make_unique<RtcEventRouteChange>(
336 network_route.connected, network_route.packet_overhead));
337 }
338 NetworkRouteChange msg;
339 msg.at_time = Timestamp::Millis(clock_->TimeInMilliseconds());
340 msg.constraints = ConvertConstraints(bitrate_config, clock_);
341 task_queue_.PostTask([this, msg, network_route] {
342 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(&task_queue_);
343 transport_overhead_bytes_per_packet_ = network_route.packet_overhead;
344 if (reset_feedback_on_route_change_) {
345 transport_feedback_adapter_.SetNetworkRoute(network_route);
346 }
347 if (controller_) {
348 PostUpdates(controller_->OnNetworkRouteChange(msg));
349 } else {
350 UpdateInitialConstraints(msg.constraints);
351 }
352 pacer()->UpdateOutstandingData(DataSize::Zero());
353 });
354 }
355}
356void RtpTransportControllerSend::OnNetworkAvailability(bool network_available) {
357 RTC_LOG(LS_VERBOSE) << "SignalNetworkState "
358 << (network_available ? "Up" : "Down");
359 NetworkAvailability msg;
360 msg.at_time = Timestamp::Millis(clock_->TimeInMilliseconds());
361 msg.network_available = network_available;
362 task_queue_.PostTask([this, msg]() {
363 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(&task_queue_);
364 if (network_available_ == msg.network_available)
365 return;
366 network_available_ = msg.network_available;
367 if (network_available_) {
368 pacer()->Resume();
369 } else {
370 pacer()->Pause();
371 }
372 pacer()->UpdateOutstandingData(DataSize::Zero());
373
374 if (controller_) {
375 control_handler_->SetNetworkAvailability(network_available_);
376 PostUpdates(controller_->OnNetworkAvailability(msg));
377 UpdateControlState();
378 } else {
379 MaybeCreateControllers();
380 }
381 });
382
383 for (auto& rtp_sender : video_rtp_senders_) {
384 rtp_sender->OnNetworkAvailability(network_available);
385 }
386}

404void RtpTransportControllerSend::OnSentPacket(
405 const rtc::SentPacket& sent_packet) {
406 task_queue_.PostTask([this, sent_packet]() {
407 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(&task_queue_);
408 absl::optional<SentPacket> packet_msg =
409 transport_feedback_adapter_.ProcessSentPacket(sent_packet);
410 pacer()->UpdateOutstandingData(
411 transport_feedback_adapter_.GetOutstandingData());
412 if (packet_msg && controller_)
413 PostUpdates(controller_->OnSentPacket(*packet_msg));
414 });
415}

423 });

426void RtpTransportControllerSend::UpdateBitrateConstraints(
427 const BitrateConstraints& updated) {
428 TargetRateConstraints msg = ConvertConstraints(updated, clock_);
429 task_queue_.PostTask([this, msg]() {
430 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(&task_queue_);
431 if (controller_) {
432 PostUpdates(controller_->OnTargetRateConstraints(msg));
433 } else {
434 UpdateInitialConstraints(msg);
435 }
436 });
437}

465absl::optional<BitrateConstraints>
466RtpTransportControllerSend::ApplyOrLiftRelayCap(bool is_relayed) {
467 DataRate cap = is_relayed ? relay_bandwidth_cap_ : DataRate::PlusInfinity();

471void RtpTransportControllerSend::OnTransportOverheadChanged(
472 size_t transport_overhead_bytes_per_packet) {
473 if (transport_overhead_bytes_per_packet >= kMaxOverheadBytes) {
474 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR) << "Transport overhead exceeds " << kMaxOverheadBytes;
475 return;
476 }
477
478 pacer()->SetTransportOverhead(
479 DataSize::Bytes(transport_overhead_bytes_per_packet));
480
481 // TODO(holmer): Call AudioRtpSenders when they have been moved to
482 // RtpTransportControllerSend.
483 for (auto& rtp_video_sender : video_rtp_senders_) {
484 rtp_video_sender->OnTransportOverheadChanged(
485 transport_overhead_bytes_per_packet);
486 }
487}

500 pacer_started_ = true;

509void RtpTransportControllerSend::OnReceivedEstimatedBitrate(uint32_t bitrate) {
510 RemoteBitrateReport msg;
511 msg.receive_time = Timestamp::Millis(clock_->TimeInMilliseconds());
512 msg.bandwidth = DataRate::BitsPerSec(bitrate);
513 task_queue_.PostTask([this, msg]() {
514 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(&task_queue_);
515 if (controller_)
516 PostUpdates(controller_->OnRemoteBitrateReport(msg));
517 });
518}
519
520void RtpTransportControllerSend::OnReceivedRtcpReceiverReport(
521 const ReportBlockList& report_blocks,
522 int64_t rtt_ms,
523 int64_t now_ms) {
524 task_queue_.PostTask([this, report_blocks, now_ms]() {
525 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(&task_queue_);
526 OnReceivedRtcpReceiverReportBlocks(report_blocks, now_ms);
527 });
528
529 task_queue_.PostTask([this, now_ms, rtt_ms]() {
530 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(&task_queue_);
531 RoundTripTimeUpdate report;
532 report.receive_time = Timestamp::Millis(now_ms);
533 report.round_trip_time = TimeDelta::Millis(rtt_ms);
534 report.smoothed = false;
535 if (controller_ && !report.round_trip_time.IsZero())
536 PostUpdates(controller_->OnRoundTripTimeUpdate(report));
537 });
538}

540void RtpTransportControllerSend::OnAddPacket(
541 const RtpPacketSendInfo& packet_info) {
542 feedback_demuxer_.AddPacket(packet_info);
543
544 Timestamp creation_time = Timestamp::Millis(clock_->TimeInMilliseconds());
545 task_queue_.PostTask([this, packet_info, creation_time]() {
546 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(&task_queue_);
547 transport_feedback_adapter_.AddPacket(
548 packet_info,
549 send_side_bwe_with_overhead_ ? transport_overhead_bytes_per_packet_ : 0,
550 creation_time);
551 });
552}
553
554void RtpTransportControllerSend::OnTransportFeedback(
555 const rtcp::TransportFeedback& feedback) {
556 feedback_demuxer_.OnTransportFeedback(feedback);
557 auto feedback_time = Timestamp::Millis(clock_->TimeInMilliseconds());
558 task_queue_.PostTask([this, feedback, feedback_time]() {
559 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(&task_queue_);
560 absl::optional<TransportPacketsFeedback> feedback_msg =
561 transport_feedback_adapter_.ProcessTransportFeedback(feedback,
562 feedback_time);
563 if (feedback_msg && controller_) {
564 PostUpdates(controller_->OnTransportPacketsFeedback(*feedback_msg));
565 }
566 pacer()->UpdateOutstandingData(
567 transport_feedback_adapter_.GetOutstandingData());
568 });
569}

571void RtpTransportControllerSend::OnRemoteNetworkEstimate(
572 NetworkStateEstimate estimate) {
573 if (event_log_) {
574 event_log_->Log(std::make_unique<RtcEventRemoteEstimate>(
575 estimate.link_capacity_lower, estimate.link_capacity_upper));
576 }
577 estimate.update_time = Timestamp::Millis(clock_->TimeInMilliseconds());
578 task_queue_.PostTask([this, estimate] {
579 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(&task_queue_);
580 if (controller_)
581 PostUpdates(controller_->OnNetworkStateEstimate(estimate));
582 });
583}
584
585void RtpTransportControllerSend::MaybeCreateControllers() {
586 RTC_DCHECK(!controller_);
587 RTC_DCHECK(!control_handler_);
588
589 if (!network_available_ || !observer_)
590 return;
591 control_handler_ = std::make_unique<CongestionControlHandler>();
592
593 initial_config_.constraints.at_time =
594 Timestamp::Millis(clock_->TimeInMilliseconds());
595 initial_config_.stream_based_config = streams_config_;
596
597 // TODO(srte): Use fallback controller if no feedback is available.
598 if (controller_factory_override_) {
599 RTC_LOG(LS_INFO) << "Creating overridden congestion controller";
600 controller_ = controller_factory_override_->Create(initial_config_);
601 process_interval_ = controller_factory_override_->GetProcessInterval();
602 } else {
603 RTC_LOG(LS_INFO) << "Creating fallback congestion controller";
604 controller_ = controller_factory_fallback_->Create(initial_config_);
605 process_interval_ = controller_factory_fallback_->GetProcessInterval();
606 }
607 UpdateControllerWithTimeInterval();
608 StartProcessPeriodicTasks();
609}
610
611void RtpTransportControllerSend::UpdateInitialConstraints(
612 TargetRateConstraints new_contraints) {
613 if (!new_contraints.starting_rate)
614 new_contraints.starting_rate = initial_config_.constraints.starting_rate;
615 RTC_DCHECK(new_contraints.starting_rate);
616 initial_config_.constraints = new_contraints;
617}
618
619void RtpTransportControllerSend::StartProcessPeriodicTasks() {
620 if (!pacer_queue_update_task_.Running()) {
621 pacer_queue_update_task_ = RepeatingTaskHandle::DelayedStart(
622 task_queue_.Get(), kPacerQueueUpdateInterval, [this]() {
623 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(&task_queue_);
624 TimeDelta expected_queue_time = pacer()->ExpectedQueueTime();
625 control_handler_->SetPacerQueue(expected_queue_time);
626 UpdateControlState();
627 return kPacerQueueUpdateInterval;
628 });
629 }
630 controller_task_.Stop();
631 if (process_interval_.IsFinite()) {
632 controller_task_ = RepeatingTaskHandle::DelayedStart(
633 task_queue_.Get(), process_interval_, [this]() {
634 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(&task_queue_);
635 UpdateControllerWithTimeInterval();
636 return process_interval_;
637 });
638 }
639}
640
641void RtpTransportControllerSend::UpdateControllerWithTimeInterval() {
642 RTC_DCHECK(controller_);
643 ProcessInterval msg;
644 msg.at_time = Timestamp::Millis(clock_->TimeInMilliseconds());
645 if (add_pacing_to_cwin_)
646 msg.pacer_queue = pacer()->QueueSizeData();
647 PostUpdates(controller_->OnProcessInterval(msg));
648}
649
650void RtpTransportControllerSend::UpdateStreamsConfig() {
651 streams_config_.at_time = Timestamp::Millis(clock_->TimeInMilliseconds());
652 if (controller_)
653 PostUpdates(controller_->OnStreamsConfig(streams_config_));
654}
655
656void RtpTransportControllerSend::PostUpdates(NetworkControlUpdate update) {
657 if (update.congestion_window) {
658 pacer()->SetCongestionWindow(*update.congestion_window);
659 }
660 if (update.pacer_config) {
661 pacer()->SetPacingRates(update.pacer_config->data_rate(),
662 update.pacer_config->pad_rate());
663 }
664 for (const auto& probe : update.probe_cluster_configs) {
665 pacer()->CreateProbeCluster(probe.target_data_rate, probe.id);
666 }
667 if (update.target_rate) {
668 control_handler_->SetTargetRate(*update.target_rate);
669 UpdateControlState();
670 }
671}
672
673void RtpTransportControllerSend::OnReceivedRtcpReceiverReportBlocks(
674 const ReportBlockList& report_blocks,
675 int64_t now_ms) {
676 if (report_blocks.empty())
677 return;
678
679 int total_packets_lost_delta = 0;
680 int total_packets_delta = 0;
681
682 // Compute the packet loss from all report blocks.
683 for (const RTCPReportBlock& report_block : report_blocks) {
684 auto it = last_report_blocks_.find(report_block.source_ssrc);
685 if (it != last_report_blocks_.end()) {
686 auto number_of_packets = report_block.extended_highest_sequence_number -
687 it->second.extended_highest_sequence_number;
688 total_packets_delta += number_of_packets;
689 auto lost_delta = report_block.packets_lost - it->second.packets_lost;
690 total_packets_lost_delta += lost_delta;
691 }
692 last_report_blocks_[report_block.source_ssrc] = report_block;
693 }
694 // Can only compute delta if there has been previous blocks to compare to. If
695 // not, total_packets_delta will be unchanged and there's nothing more to do.
696 if (!total_packets_delta)
697 return;
698 int packets_received_delta = total_packets_delta - total_packets_lost_delta;
699 // To detect lost packets, at least one packet has to be received. This check
700 // is needed to avoid bandwith detection update in
701 // VideoSendStreamTest.SuspendBelowMinBitrate
702
703 if (packets_received_delta < 1)
704 return;
705 Timestamp now = Timestamp::Millis(now_ms);
706 TransportLossReport msg;
707 msg.packets_lost_delta = total_packets_lost_delta;
708 msg.packets_received_delta = packets_received_delta;
709 msg.receive_time = now;
710 msg.start_time = last_report_block_time_;
711 msg.end_time = now;
712 if (controller_)
713 PostUpdates(controller_->OnTransportLossReport(msg));
714 last_report_block_time_ = now;
715}
